{"word":"θρηνέω","slug":"θρηνέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θρηνέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:θρῆνος'><el>θρῆνος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to sing a dirge, to wail</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn., <el>ἀοιδὴν ἐθρήνεον</el> <i>were singing</i> a dirge, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>ὠιδάς, ἐπωιδάς θρ.</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>ἅλις μοι τεθρήνηται</el>, <a href='S:impersonal'>impers.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> objecti, <i>to wail for, lament</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; so also <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be lamented</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}